arketing and search optimisation.  I&#39;d trust the spec sheet more than anything I read on Amazon </span></div></div>", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1450155721059729622", "author": "Aqueum", "author_handle": "aqueum.", "user_id": "709725491875020820", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/709725491875020820/a49fe1d2ccef21aa7b4b2572b995269c.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Monday, December 15, 2025 11:01 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-12-15 11:01 a.m.", "text": "What power are they setting their units to, and what losses do they have?", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>What power are they setting their units to, and what losses do they have?</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}, {"id": "1454864887091171398", "author": "Buzzard", "author_handle": "xraider01", "user_id": "427108378419003395", "avatar": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/427108378419003395/1f6020c625f6135c768f618f4ea0fdb3.png?size=512", "timestamp": "Sunday, December 28, 2025 10:53 a.m.", "timestamp_short": "2025-12-28 10:53 a.m.", "text": "I remember a video by Heltec regarding the v4 and I think 27dbm is advertised on the basis of 3.7v input from a battery - so with USB power and 5v that might explain 30dbm? (edited)", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>I remember a video by Heltec regarding the v4 and I think 27dbm is advertised on the basis of 3.7v input from a battery - so with USB power and 5v that might explain 30dbm?</span> <span class=chatlog__edited-timestamp title=\"Sunday, December 28, 2025 10:54 a.m.\">(edited)</span></div>", "embeds_html": [], "attachments_html": [], "reactions_html": "", "reply_html": "", "forwarded_html": ""}]}